positions.comment: Entered the Caledonian Canal at Corpach sea loch. Ben Nevis in sight.
Well into the canal now been up Neptunes Staircase.
Reached Fort Augustus in Caledonian Canal. Weather been good so far.
Loch Ness- Sun Blazing - Passing the castle - beautifull.
Loch Ness completed - no sightings of monster.
Inverness - 1 more lock b4 open sea. Weather warm but windy.
Left Canal tis morning - booh. Whitehills now and to Peterhead tomorrow.
Arrived Peterhead 18.55 motorsailed all the way as no wind
Arrived Arbroath passage very lumpy F5 on the nose a lot of the way.
Edinburgh is here. Awa fur a birthday/anniversary dram.
On the water again, anchored at Eyemouth overnight.
Berthed in Sunderland marina for the night weather V hot.
Berhed in Whitby marina weather V hot town looks interesting.
Todays sail of 77Nm to Grimsby cancelled due to high winds.
Arrived Grimsby after 12 Hr motoring. Big swell no wind main slatting.
Arrived Ijmuiden Holland trip time 26.5 Hrs sea rough but arrived safely.
Through sea lock stopping just inside Noordzee Kanaal for a few days.
Now at W.V.IJmond marina - very nice and very hot.
Now at Spaarndam weather still hot but windy today.
Now at Haarlem weather still V.hot .
Please ignore last report. Now at Haarlem weather still V.hot .
Just ouside Amsterdam. Still v warm. 10 Mins walk to centre. Free mooring...
Visiting Aelous Marina just opp Amsterdam.
Just arrived in Hoorn saw some lovely sailing barges on the way.
Still here - weather rainy then sunny then rainy then sunny ???
Moved to an anchorage for the night tomorrow Monnickendam.
Arrived Monnickendam - sun is still blazing - how long can it last?
Arrived Lelystad after a cracking 3 Hr sail across the IJsselmeer.
Moved marinas to visit Kampen a medieval Dutch town.
Popped up the canal to Eldburg - a walled 13th century town.
In Hardervijk alongside town quay, windmill in sight and sunny too.
Moved to Spakenburg.
Back in Harderwijk making our way back to Hoorn.
Now in Urk, another cloudless sunny day.
Back in Hoorn, no more reports until Aril 2006. Tot Ziens.
